{Speech 2}{}{Hi! My name is Mom and I'm running this place. We serve the most tasty dishes to the north of New-Reno.@@Hello! My name is Mom and I'm running this place. We serve the most tasty dishes to the north of New-Reno.@@Hello! Name's Mom, and this is my restaurant. We serve the most tasty dishes to the north of New-Reno.}
{Speech 2 Answer 3}{}{It's nice to meet you, Mom. I'm @pname@.}
{Speech 3}{}{What would you like to talk about?@@What is it?}
{Speech 3 Answer 41}{}{I came from James, he wants you to pay for the goods now.}
{Speech 3 Answer 39}{}{I'd like to talk about the ghost.}
{Speech 3 Answer 12}{}{I've brought you radscorp tails! [You give Mom 4 tails]}
{Speech 3 Answer 31}{}{Virginia won't bother you anymore.}
{Speech 3 Answer 4}{}{You're not my mom.}
{Speech 3 Answer 6}{}{What are the dishes?}
{Speech 3 Answer 11}{}{What's there to do here?}
{Speech 3 Answer 13}{}{Tell me which towns are nearby.}
{Speech 3 Answer 18}{}{What are the news lately?}
{Speech 4}{}{I know that. But everyone calls me that. Heck, I even treat people like they're my kin - long as you obey my rules that is.}
{Speech 4 Answer 5}{}{Rules?}
{Speech 5}{}{That's right. No stealing, no cursing, and no fighting - not in my shop you don't. 'Cause if'n you do, out you'll go. I like things peaceful here.}
{Speech 5 Answer 3}{}{I see. Let me ask you something else.}
{Speech 5 Answer Exit}{}{I see. Later, Mom.}
{Speech 6}{}{Here, choose one. [She checks the menu] We have rat-pie, rat-loaf and dish of the day.}
{Speech 6 Answer 7}{}{Uh, could I get something without so much rat in it?}
{Speech 6 Answer 9}{}{Rat-loaf.}
{Speech 6 Answer 9*}{}{Rat-pie.}
{Speech 6 Answer 8}{}{Dish of the day?}
{Speech 7}{}{You could have the spaghetti. It doesn't have too much rat in it - just the sauce, that's all.}
{Speech 7 Answer 9}{}{Well, OK, I guess I'll have the spaghetti with rat-sauce.}
{Speech 8}{}{You're in luck. We're having radscorpion stew.@@We're having braised pig-rat.@@We're serving steamed radscorpion tails in drawn butter.@@Cabbage soup is all I've got right now.@@Fresh brahmin fries!@@Pipin' hot gecko pie, comin' up.@@Flank steak.@@Well-marbled molerat.@@Fricasseed floater.@@Filet mignon.@@Medallions of grilled gecko.@@Mantis marsala.@@Molerat manicotti.@@Brahmin en brochette.@@Radscorpion en croute.@@Uh, I'm not sure, but it tastes like chicken.@@Centaur chops, my specialty.@@It's a surprise.@@It's Smeat!@@Really?}
{Speech 8 Answer 9}{}{Great!@@My fav!@@Ummm... sounds good!}
{Speech 9}{}{I'll get you a nice helping right away. That'll be $15.}
{Speech 9 Answer 3}{}{I don't have enough money right now. Let me ask you a question instead.}
{Speech 9 Answer 10}{}{$15 for rat? You've got to be crazy. Heck, around the village we charge much more for a nice juicy one. That's a deal.}
{Speech 9 Answer 10*}{}{Well, OK. Here's your money.}
{Speech 9 Answer 3*}{}{I think I've changed my mind. Let me ask you a question instead.}
{Speech 9 Answer Exit}{}{I think I'll come back later. Goodbye.}
{Speech 10}{}{You have quite an appetite there. I love to see a healthy eater. Will that do it for you?}
{Speech 10 Answer 6}{}{Not a chance, Mom. I want more.}
{Speech 10 Answer 3}{}{Sure will. Let me ask you something, Mom.}
{Speech 10 Answer Exit}{}{That's it for now. Goodbye, Mom.}
{Speech 11}{}{Well, I sure need someone to bring me 4 radscorpion tails. I need that for my special meal. If you bring me them, you'll get a free meal!}
{Speech 11 Answer 3}{}{Let me think about it. In the meantime, let me ask you about something else.}
{Speech 11 Answer Exit}{}{Sure, I don't mind.}
{Speech 11 Answer Exit*}{}{Uh, sorry, Mom. I can't. Goodbye.}
{Speech 12}{}{That was good work. You must have worked up quite an appetite. I have a real treat for you as a reward. A combination plate of the best darn food I have here, just for you.}
{Speech 12 Answer 3}{}{That sounds great! Let me at it!}
{Speech 12 Answer Exit}{}{Gee, Mom. I don't think I can eat just now, but thanks anyhow. Goodbye.}
{Speech 13}{}{There are number of towns to north-west, east and far south-east. Which direction are you planning to move in?}
{Speech 13 Answer 16}{}{North-west.}
{Speech 13 Answer 14}{}{South-east.}
{Speech 13 Answer 15}{}{East.}
{Speech 13 Answer 3}{}{Let me ask you something else.}
{Speech 13 Answer Exit}{}{You know, I'd better not ask but actually move in some direction.}
{Speech 14}{}{There's this miners town to south-east, Redding, and far deep is New Reno. It's quite unpeaceful there, a lot of crime.}
{Speech 14 Answer 13}{}{I see. What's about other ones?}
{Speech 14 Answer Exit}{}{Thanks for the info. Goodbye.}
{Speech 15}{}{If you go east, you'll see a small town called Modoc. Vault City is a bit farther.}
{Speech 15 Answer 13}{}{I see. What's about other ones?}
{Speech 15 Answer Exit}{}{Thanks for the info. Goodbye.}
{Speech 16}{}{There's a town called Klamath, it's near to north-west from here. That's town of trappers, they hunt geckos, those little hellish lizards. People say they've called a sort of beer after those lizards, it's "Golden Gecko". It passes for the best beer in the district, but you can get it only in the bar of the same name in Klamath. A bit farther from Klamath there is a village called Arroyo. Only savages lived there earlier, but they're quite civilized now. By the way, Chosen One is from Arroyo. He and his predecessor have saved the world...}
{Speech 16 Answer 17}{}{Chosen One? Haven't heard of him.}
{Speech 16 Answer 13}{}{I see. What's about other ones?}
{Speech 16 Answer Exit}{}{Thanks for the info. Goodbye.}
{Speech 17}{}{I got heartwarming memories about him... He was very nice. It's a pity he has lost without a sign after saving his village dwellers.}
{Speech 17 Answer 13}{}{I see. I'd like to ask you about them towns once again.}
{Speech 17 Answer Exit}{}{Has lost? That's interesting... Thanks, Mom, I gotta leave, do some business. If I meet him I'll let you know.}
{Speech 18}{}{There're lots of things happened in the past years... Metzger's murder, starting the church... Becky has given away the bar helm of state to Leanna and has become Mayor. Brotherhood of Steel has established the orphanage, Lara started a gunshop. Flick's nest belongs to Fred and it has become a nice store. Also Tubby's missing.}
{Speech 18 Answer 19}{}{Tell me about Metzger.}
{Speech 18 Answer 20}{}{Starting the church?}
{Speech 18 Answer 21}{}{What's with Becky's?}
{Speech 18 Answer 22}{}{Tell me about the Brotherhood and orpanage.}
{Speech 18 Answer 23}{}{What's with Flick's?}
{Speech 18 Answer 24}{}{What happened to Tubby?}
{Speech 18 Answer 25}{}{[More]}
{Speech 19}{}{Well, he was a major slaver and controlled all the spivvery in Den in the past. He was a terrible man. And he ran a whole gang of thugs. But luckily he was killed by the glorious traveller also known as Chosen One. One fine day Metzger and everyone who was around him were found dead in the office. The city hall runs in the slavery guild building now.}
{Speech 19 Answer 18}{}{What else happened in the city?}
{Speech 19 Answer Exit}{}{Very interesting, but I gotta go.}
{Speech 20}{}{Yep. Some time ago, a perky girl named Lara took away her rival Tyler from the old church and tried to replace him for Metzger. In spite of her youth she tried to play her own game. Her gang stationed itself in the church, but as soon as Brotherhood of Steel started to influence Den she was asked politely to leave. And the church has become... surprise! A church. Now it has the altar and the priest, Darksome Cliff. And even the parish.}
{Speech 20 Answer 18}{}{What else happened in the city?}
{Speech 20 Answer 22}{}{What's that Brotherhood of Steel?}
{Speech 20 Answer Exit}{}{Hmmm, sounds interesting, but I must leave now.}
{Speech 21}{}{Becky's casino is well-being as always. She's not the bartender anymore. It's Leanna now, her good old friend. Becky was fed with her idling and she hired her. Becky herself is all in the politic field now, she stood for City Mayor lately and won the race. But well... some people think that she's behind a man from Brotherhood who started all this election thing...}
{Speech 21 Answer 18}{}{What else happened in the city?}
{Speech 21 Answer 22}{}{What's that Brotherhood?}
{Speech 21 Answer Exit}{}{Hmmm, sounds interesting, but I must leave now.}
{Speech 22}{}{Brotherhood of Steel has built an orphanage. The former Metzger's slavers guild building was reconstructed into the City Hall. The ophanage was built at the ruins of the building where slaves were held. Becky runs it. Obviously, the Brotherhood has its own interests in our town. Children from the orphanage attend the Sunday school. Members of the Brotherhood educate them in the special classes. People say that it's a very strong organization; at least they have such weapons and armor that... Ummm... [Her face becomes full of suggestion] They almost praise the technology. It seems that they're growing the upcoming gunners and scientists generation.}
{Speech 22 Answer 18}{}{What else happened in the city?}
{Speech 22 Answer Exit}{}{Very interesting, but I gotta go.}
{Speech 23}{}{Flick had his loans over his head. The one who saved him from this debtors pit was Fred, no one really knows how he got that rich. He bought Flick's nest and reconstructed it into a fine store. They've said their goodbyes to all the junkies, set the counters and now work with traders from the outer world. Fred hired Flick as a helpmate.}
{Speech 23 Answer 18}{}{What else happened in the city?}
{Speech 23 Answer Exit}{}{Very interesting, but I gotta go.}
{Speech 24}{}{Tubby's disappeared... as well as Tubby himself. He was fond of jet and others' wives too much, which leaded to complete bust and overwhelming loans. Day by day his shop was turning into a nest for those junkies kicked out from Flick's. People say that someone has found a crippled vagabond's body a bit north of Den that looked a bit like Tubby, but these are rumours... And you can't trust them.}
{Speech 24 Answer 18}{}{What else happened in the city?}
{Speech 24 Answer Exit}{}{Very interesting, but I gotta go.}
{Speech 25}{}{Smitty, my husband, develops his business... Everything's going fairly well. Drug and alcohol abuse is out town's major problems. And now that damn whore Virginia appeared!}
{Speech 25 Answer 26}{}{So Lara started a gunshop?}
{Speech 25 Answer 27}{}{Are you married with Smitty?}
{Speech 25 Answer 28}{}{What's about that Virginia?}
{Speech 25 Answer 29}{}{Where are the drugs and the alcohol coming from?}
{Speech 25 Answer Exit}{}{Thanks for the info. Byes.}
{Speech 26}{}{Lara started the gunshop at her former HQ. People don't have an opportunity to shoot and kill now, the Brotherhood of Steel won't let them, so they have to search how to earn some money. The prices are rough a bit, but you pay for quality. Besides that I noticed that Lara started to take an interest in politics - she's not okay with the Den official government existance and she'd like to get rid of it. That girl is pure anarchist, just like her surroundings.}
{Speech 26 Answer 18}{}{What else happened in the city?}
{Speech 26 Answer Exit}{}{Very interesting, but I gotta go.}
{Speech 27}{}{Me and smitty were helping each other with the business before, but then it all reeled and whirled and... [Seems that she blushes] You know how this kind of things go. Father Darksome Cliff ran the procedure. Smitty's business is doing good; some time ago that Highwayman scorching across the wasteland served as a good ad for him. People from our district have brought him a lot of junk, and he's even managed to fix something. Smitty hired some assistants, cleared up the junk laying here and there and now he's known as the best repairman of the surroundings. The most interesting thing he has is that robot Mr. Handy, I have absolutely no idea where it is from. Seems that it's the most important idol for children, except the Brotherhood. [She laughs] It's shabby and almost working but Smitty can't find enough courage to repair it and make some use of it. Or maybe sell it, who knows.}
{Speech 27 Answer 18}{}{What else happened in the city?}
{Speech 27 Answer Exit}{}{Hmmm, sounds interesting, but I must leave now.}
{Speech 28}{}{The only one that bothers me is that whore Virginia that is always hanging around my establishment. She's only 18 but she's the first prostitute in town. Sells drugs and body. She likes to tattle with the customers a lot. She often claims that she's misunderstood and was born in the wrong place at the wrong time... In short terms, I'd like her to vanish for some time at least!}
{Speech 28 Answer 18}{}{What else happened in the city?}
{Speech 28 Answer 30}{}{Would you like me to solve that problem?}
{Speech 28 Answer Exit}{}{Very interesting, but I gotta go.}
{Speech 29}{}{Drugs and alcohol slightly fall away from Den. There are a lot of factors working towards it: a good man in charge, existance of so-called police as the Brotherhood of Steel that has its own plans for Northern wasteland regions. But some inhabitants sell both drugs and alcohol. The Brotherhood would appreciate any kind of help in knocking those people out, I think.}
{Speech 29 Answer 18}{}{What else happened in the city?}
{Speech 29 Answer Exit}{}{Hmmm, sounds interesting, but I must leave now.}
{Speech 30}{}{Yes, I'd be happy if she disappears. Of course without any violence. Remember that!}
{Speech 30 Answer Exit}{}{I'll see what I can do.}
{Speech 30 Answer 18}{}{No, I'm not interested. Tell me something else.}
{Speech 30 Answer Exit*}{}{No, I think I'll be going.}
{Speech 31}{}{You did your best! Let me treat you some meal.}
{Speech 31 Answer 3}{}{Oh, thanks!}
{Speech 31 Answer Exit}{}{Thanks, but I'm not hungry.}
